section.t:
A Restricted-A-Label is a DNS-Label which satisfies all
        the following conditions:


	  the DNS-Label is a valid A-Label according to ;

	  the derived property value of all code points, as defined
	    by , is PVALID;

	  the general category of all code points, is one of {
	    Ll, Lo, Lm, Mn }.


	This new specification reflects current practice in
	registration of TLD names by the IANA, extended to accommodate
	IDNs.
